During a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Josh Earnest addressed a range of topics including the criticism of President Obama's handling of the campaign against ISIS, the situation in Brussels, the closure of Guantanamo Bay prison, the tax-inversion deal between Pfizer and Allergan, and the upcoming meeting between President Obama and French President Hollande. Earnest also discussed the issue of surveillance of mosques and the refugee program. He emphasized that the United States is committed to working with its coalition partners to defeat ISIS and that the President is optimistic about reaching a comprehensive climate agreement. Earnest also mentioned that the United States is working towards a political transition in Syria and that President Assad has lost legitimacy to lead the country.